<b>Subject:</b> UO<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2173" TARGET=_self>Re: Hmmm</A> (Ice)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I am not at all after making PvP less popular(may have misunderstood your post). As for warriors having better loot then mages, that is a class choice and I am indifferent to its outcome(although any less looting would piss me off). My solutions are for curbing the Naked Mages. If you know that putting on your magic platemail of wizard busting will help you whoop the next wizard you see, you might wear it if the wizard lost something for attacking you. The current problem is that a wizard with nothing can bind close by, come at ya, get his ass kicked, respawn and mem, and attack again without losing ANYTHING. If a wizard kept coming at ya losing XP someday he will stop coming. The only problem I see are the people whom do not wish to lose XP when they were PKed at low life after fighting on NPC. I think that's just too bad for them(it happens), but anytime you die there should be consequences.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
